Note:
This file handles core LIR type definitions and LIR data structures.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process core LIR type definitions and LIR data structure management
- Handle LIR instruction types and LIR virtual register types
- Manage LIR memory addressing types and LIR optimization types
- Process LIR metadata types and LIR code generation types

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Core LIR types enable low-level representation for code generation
- Proper LIR type handling ensures correct LIR data structure management
- Core LIR types support enables Runa compilation for register allocation

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Core LIR type definitions and LIR data structure management
- LIR instruction types and LIR virtual register types
- LIR memory addressing types and LIR optimization types
- LIR metadata types and LIR code generation types

Dependencies:
- Imports HIR types for type information reuse
- Imports memory/layout.runa for OWNED HEAP allocation (Tier 3)
- Imports collections/list.runa for instruction and block management
- Imports collections/dictionary.runa for value tracking
- Imports core/string_core.runa for debug printing
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as MemoryCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dictionary
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/ordered_map.runa" as OrderedMap
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils

