@Implementation
Sets is_external (offset 112) to 1 and writes library_name/alias_name/
convention_id into the P2-D extension slots (offsets 144/152/160). The
callee owns no copies - the caller is expected to pass already-owned
strings or stable interned pointers; LIR does not duplicate them again
because they typically originate from the import declaration itself.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Four 8-byte writes; called once per external function during HIR-to-LIR
lowering. Not on the per-instruction hot path.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
