    If function is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let return_type be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with function, 64
    If return_type is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
get_frame_size reads the total aligned stack frame size of an
LIRFunction by following the stack_frame pointer (offset 72) to the
StackFrame record and loading its frame_size field (offset 0). Backends
use this value to emit prologue stack adjustment. A function whose
frame has not been finalized (or a leaf function with no frame) reports
0, which backends translate to "no stack adjustment".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. NULL-guard the function pointer.
2. Load the stack_frame pointer at offset 72; return 0 when absent.
3. Load and return frame_size at StackFrame offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Two dependent memory loads. Inlinable. Called once per function during
prologue emission, so cost is negligible.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
NULL-safe at both the function and stack-frame layers. The value is a
byte count produced by lir_finalize_stack_frame; backends must treat it
as data, never as a pointer.
@End Security_Scope

