@Reasoning
get_has_calls reports whether an LIRFunction performs any calls, derived
from the is_leaf flag at offset 120 (is_leaf = 1 means the function
makes no calls). Backends consult this to decide whether the prologue
must save the return-address register (e.g. $ra on MIPS, lr on PowerPC)
and whether frame setup can be elided.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. NULL-guard the function pointer; a NULL function reports 0 (no
   calls) so callers take the cheaper leaf path on malformed input
   rather than emitting save/restore code for an absent function.
2. Load is_leaf at offset 120 and return its logical inverse: 1 when
   is_leaf is 0, otherwise 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One memory load plus one compare. Inlinable.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
NULL-safe defensive load. The flag is maintained by the LIR builder
when lowering call instructions; this accessor performs no scanning of
instruction lists.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_has_calls" that takes function as Integer returns Integer:
    If function is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let is_leaf be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with function, 120
    If is_leaf is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Adds an instruction to the end of a basic block.
Updates the block's instruction count.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. NULL-guard both function and instruction.
2. Resolve the block pointer from block_id via lir_get_block (which also
   bounds-checks block_id).
3. Append the instruction pointer to the block's instructions List
   (offset 16) and increment instruction_count (offset 24) in lockstep so
   any downstream reader sees a consistent count/list pair.
4. Clear the function's is_leaf flag (offset 120) when the appended
   instruction is a call (lir_is_call), so get_has_calls reflects
   reality for backend prologue decisions.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One List.append plus two memory loads and one memory store. Hot during
LIR construction; the lockstep increment avoids any second pass to
recompute counts.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Rejects NULL parameters and invalid block IDs before mutating the block
contents. Failure surfaces a diagnostic and returns 0, leaving the
function in its prior state.
@End Security_Scope

