@Reasoning
Creates an empty stack frame for a function with default settings.
The frame will be populated during register allocation and stack slot assignment.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Allocate 80 bytes on the OWNED HEAP for the StackFrame header.
2. Initialize all ten fields: frame_size, local_area_size, spill_area_size,
   and arg_area_size start at zero (populated by stack-slot assignment),
   alignment is hard-set to 16 for x86-64 ABI compliance, uses_frame_pointer
   defaults to 1 (the prologue lowering may demote this later if the
   function is a leaf with no spills).
3. Create empty callee_saved_regs List, local_offsets OrderedMap, and
   spill_offsets OrderedMap so allocator passes have stable containers to
   write into (both maps are integer-keyed, so Dictionary is forbidden).
4. Wire the new frame into the LIRFunction's stack_frame slot (offset 72).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One frame-sized allocation plus three container allocations (List +
two OrderedMaps). Called once per function and never on a per-instruction
path.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
NULL-guards both the function pointer and the frame allocation. Failure
surfaces a diagnostic and returns 0; the function's existing stack_frame
slot is not overwritten in that case.
@End Security_Scope

